’ђђЪ Title: title: Nushell 2019 Survey Results
Path: Nushell 2019 Survey Results
Content:




Recently, we ran a short survey to see how you were feeling about 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell] Nushell
. We wanted to give a very hearty "thank you!" to everyone who participated. These surveys are a great way to gather information about how people are feeling, where they're happy, and where they feel there are pain points.
In total, 
160
 people responded. An impressive amount for a project still in its first few months in the public.
—Щ`archive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2019-11-23-nushell-survey-results.mdЩ@f0b72517271f98bb06ff9176fe0c7f422a25d6cb32cf7489001abc44bf318efaЩ"title: Nushell 2019 Survey Results‘®Do you use Nu?ЪЙ63.1% don't use, 24.4% use but stopped, 12.5% use
The survey welcomed both users and non-users of Nu. In our first question, we wanted to see how many folks are using Nu already. Perhaps unsurprising for a project still missing major functionality, most respondents aren't users, yet. As we'll see, there are themes around what people are waiting for before they jump in.
But first, let's take a look at the responses from folks how are currently using Nu.
